The course is a training of methodology, preparing to the bachelor's independent research. The aim of this course is to help the student to find his subject of research, to discuss about it, to give some advices to realise a structured work, to discuss about agenda and about methodology and presentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Developing individual research skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student is able to - formulate explicitly the problems of his research - use a methodology to develop his research - explain the problems of his research - draw up a plan  - use a well-adapted vocabulary  - write an introduction and a conclusion - create a bibliography - consider methodological problems of agenda - write a report with an effective logical structure
